	   <tr><td colspan=2>"Let's take another look into these balancing issues you're always freaking out about, Verant."<br><br>Have you played a high level caster before and tried to melee? 15dmg/18dly just means that you get to miss a lot more often and on occasion get in a 15dmg hit. This does NOT affect game balance. Heck, 18dmg/15dly on a caster item wouldn't unbalance the game.<br><br>Let me put it in ranger terms. Say you gave to a lv 60 ranger, a hybrid version of sunstrike, one of the best dmg/dly spells for the best nuking class, wizards. 1600dmg/450mana 7 seconds to cast.<br><br>Now, say that you the ranger cast this spell, but it gets fully resisted 95% of the time (that's 450 mana for 0 dmg and 7 sec. melee wasted), you get 100dmg 3% of the time, 500dmg 2% of the time, and 1600dmg 1% of the time.<br><br>Would you really waste your melee time and limited mana pool on this spell? Btw, those figures work out to rougly 29dmg per cast on average if you had infinite mana and cast it over and over again.<br><br>I guess what I'm saying is, you can put whatever stats on caster weapons and it won't matter worth a donkey's ass because we can't melee =)<br><br>Amoran<br>57 Enchanter<br>Quellious<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
