	   <tr><td colspan=2>Caster weapons will (I assume from now on) have the best ratios in the game for one reason. Casters are horrible at melee. An offense cap of 145, individual weapon caps of 110-115 (I forget which) does NOT equal a powerhouse of melee. Don't forget, casters get no primary hand melee bonus, no double attack, no bash, kick, stun etc. These items have some limited uses as weapons. Skeletons chasing you down/interrupting your spells is a good one. Sometimes I like to get up and whack at the mob a few times. Its fun. Giving casters a weapon that is not only fast but hits harder than 10 damage isn't a bad thing :)<br><br>Also, if you remember, Paladins and Shadow Knights get the best 1 handed weapons in the game for actual melee. This is because they can't dual wield. Casters get even better because we can't hit :)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
